{"event_id": "db7325d561d94c64baaaee915fbbf8d5", "event_type": "tool_called", "event_version": 1, "mission_id": "20260402-110030-106651-tiny-live-canary", "model": "openai/gpt-4.1-mini", "node_id": "root.step-01-write-operator-note-on-open-eywa", "node_path": "/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/open-eywa/missions/live-canaries/20260402-110030-106651-tiny-live-canary/tree/root/children/step-01-write-operator-note-on-open-eywa", "parent_node_id": null, "payload": {"arguments": {"content": "# Operator Note on Open-Eywa\n\n## What is Open-Eywa?\nOpen-Eywa is a distributed, hierarchical task execution system designed to manage complex workflows by breaking them down into smaller, manageable units called nodes. Each node represents a discrete unit of work that can be executed independently or in coordination with other nodes. This architecture enables scalable, reliable, and traceable task execution across multiple agents or systems.\n\n## Why is the Node the Durable Unit of Work?\nThe node is the durable unit of work because it encapsulates all the necessary information, state, and context required to complete a specific task. Nodes are designed to be self-contained and persistent, allowing the system to pause, resume, or recover work without losing progress. This durability ensures robustness in the face of failures, interruptions, or distributed execution environments.\n\n## Which Mission Files Should a Human Inspect First?\nTo understand the mission and effectively operate within Open-Eywa, a human operator should start by inspecting the following mission files:\n\n1. **input/context.md** - Provides the overall context and background for the mission.\n2. **input/parent-instructions.md** - Contains the high-level task instructions and goals.\n3. **output/state.md** - Shows the current state and progress of the node.\n4. **output/final-output.md** - Contains the final results or outputs generated by the node.\n\nReviewing these files will give a clear understanding of the mission objectives, the current status, and the outputs produced, enabling effective monitoring and intervention if needed.\n\n---\n\nThis note should help operators quickly grasp the purpose and structure of Open-Eywa, the significance of nodes, and the key files to focus on for mission comprehension and management.", "path": "output/final-output.md"}, "tool_name": "write_file"}, "role": "worker", "run_id": "run-001", "timestamp_utc": "2026-04-02T05:15:47.183531Z", "variant": null}
